and we are the rock racks and we like to party.

1056
00:46:13,219 --> 00:46:15,219
The mighty, mighty rock racks.

1057
00:46:15,219 --> 00:46:18,419
Doesn't matter what you say, we will beat you anyway.

1058
00:46:20,819 --> 00:46:21,699
And they go on.

1059
00:46:21,699 --> 00:46:22,579
So they both know it.

1060
00:46:22,579 --> 00:46:25,940
They both, they both like, yeah, like, like they learned it together.

1061
00:46:27,699 --> 00:46:31,059
Are you sure one of them is a doppelganger?

1062
00:46:31,059 --> 00:46:32,259
He's the doppelganger.

1063
00:46:32,259 --> 00:46:33,219
No, he is.

1064
00:46:33,219 --> 00:46:34,579
Are you sure you're not just twins?

1065
00:46:37,460 --> 00:46:37,699
No.

1066
00:46:38,500 --> 00:46:40,739
I'm going to come join this long pause.

1067
00:46:40,739 --> 00:46:41,460
Incredible conversation now.

1068
00:46:41,460 --> 00:46:42,099
Who are you?

1069
00:46:43,619 --> 00:46:44,980
That's a loaded question.

1070
00:46:44,980 --> 00:46:46,739
Do you hire that one too?

1071
00:46:46,739 --> 00:46:48,980
Okay, you guys can't afford any of us.

1072
00:46:48,980 --> 00:46:50,019
We've been over this.

1073
00:46:50,019 --> 00:46:51,619
You don't know what we can afford.

1074
00:46:51,619 --> 00:46:52,099
Yeah.

1075
00:46:52,099 --> 00:46:53,139
Hey, here's the thing.

1076
00:46:53,139 --> 00:46:54,259
Empty your pockets.

1077
00:46:55,139 --> 00:46:55,940
Well, I left my-

1078
00:46:55,940 --> 00:46:57,619
Empty your pockets.

1079
00:46:57,619 --> 00:46:59,460
Left my satchel.

1080
00:46:59,460 --> 00:46:59,960
Empty up.

1081
00:47:00,659 --> 00:47:01,619
Empty their pockets.

1082
00:47:02,739 --> 00:47:04,739
Does one of them have government issued ID?

1083
00:47:04,739 --> 00:47:07,539
Yeah, is there going to be just a business card that says I'm a doppelganger?

1084
00:47:07,539 --> 00:47:12,179
I'm wondering, does one have nothing in his pockets and the other one have things?

1085
00:47:12,179 --> 00:47:18,259
Both empty their pockets, a few random pieces of coin.

1086
00:47:18,260 --> 00:47:20,260
I need to know more about doppelgangers, you guys.

1087
00:47:21,700 --> 00:47:25,620
So philosophically, are you guys just mad?

1088
00:47:27,700 --> 00:47:28,500
Why are you fighting?

1089
00:47:29,220 --> 00:47:30,180
It should be a compliment.

1090
00:47:30,180 --> 00:47:32,180
Someone wants to be exactly like you.

1091
00:47:32,180 --> 00:47:32,820
Seems nice.

1092
00:47:32,820 --> 00:47:34,660
Except a doppelganger sneaks into your life,

1093
00:47:34,660 --> 00:47:38,020
murders you, and tries to take over your whole existence.

1094
00:47:38,020 --> 00:47:39,540
Oh, that doesn't sound good.

1095
00:47:39,540 --> 00:47:40,420
Oh, that is bad.

1096
00:47:40,420 --> 00:47:40,740
Yeah.

1097
00:47:40,740 --> 00:47:42,820
What do you got going on that's worth taking over?

1098
00:47:43,620 --> 00:47:45,140
Yeah, no, great question.

1099
00:47:45,140 --> 00:47:46,900
Are you high up in your plan?

1100
00:47:46,900 --> 00:47:50,500
Yeah, well, I mean, I've got, you know, that big promotion coming to work.

1101
00:47:51,700 --> 00:47:55,780
And clearly it's next in line to the big boss.

1102
00:47:57,380 --> 00:47:58,260
It's the Rock Racks.

1103
00:47:58,980 --> 00:47:59,700
Whose name is?

1104
00:48:00,340 --> 00:48:01,300
Gwendover.

1105
00:48:01,300 --> 00:48:02,180
Gwendover.

1106
00:48:04,260 --> 00:48:05,780
Gwendover Rock Rack.

1107
00:48:05,780 --> 00:48:07,940
Russ defaulting to a G name?

1108
00:48:07,940 --> 00:48:08,740
It's been a while.

1109
00:48:08,740 --> 00:48:09,619
I'm amazed.

1110
00:48:10,660 --> 00:48:11,160
Okay.

1111
00:48:12,980 --> 00:48:14,820
Got anyone special at home?

1112
00:48:15,620 --> 00:48:17,460
Well, not right now.

1113
00:48:18,340 --> 00:48:19,380
Oh, no, it's okay.

1114
00:48:19,380 --> 00:48:20,420
There's nothing wrong with that.

1115
00:48:20,420 --> 00:48:21,539
You don't have to rub it in.

1116
00:48:21,539 --> 00:48:23,780
Geez, what'd you hire them just to make me feel bad?

1117
00:48:23,780 --> 00:48:25,780
No one here is hired.

1118
00:48:25,780 --> 00:48:28,980
Well, it's very convenient that the three of you has come along

1119
00:48:28,980 --> 00:48:31,780
and you're trying to stop me from killing this doppelganger.

1120
00:48:32,420 --> 00:48:34,740
Do you have a mom or a sibling?

1121
00:48:34,740 --> 00:48:36,180
Someone who might know something about you.

1122
00:48:36,180 --> 00:48:38,180
It's awfully hard for us to tell you two apart.

1123
00:48:38,180 --> 00:48:44,100
Both of them say at the same time, yeah, we have, yeah, sure.

1124
00:48:44,820 --> 00:48:45,700
Have parents?

1125
00:48:46,580 --> 00:48:48,019
Oh my God.

1126
00:48:49,140 --> 00:48:50,260
I smack both of them.

1127
00:48:51,860 --> 00:48:53,059
You guys are just twins.

1128
00:48:54,260 --> 00:48:56,100
Oh, you little bitches.

1129
00:48:56,100 --> 00:48:56,980
Come on.

1130
00:48:56,980 --> 00:48:59,940
If you're trying to rob us, I swear to God,

1131
00:48:59,940 --> 00:49:02,260
we've got a Wormling back there that's probably made

1132
00:49:02,900 --> 00:49:05,539
roasted shish kebabs out of whoever else you're working with.

1133
00:49:06,260 --> 00:49:06,980
I hit them again.

1134
00:49:08,340 --> 00:49:09,700
I'm not trying to rob you.

1135
00:49:09,700 --> 00:49:10,740
I'm trying to kill him.

1136
00:49:12,180 --> 00:49:12,980
Piss me off.

1137
00:49:13,619 --> 00:49:14,980
So you were trying to kill him?

1138
00:49:14,980 --> 00:49:15,699
Yeah.

1139
00:49:15,699 --> 00:49:17,219
Well, I mean, he's trying to kill me too.

1140
00:49:18,420 --> 00:49:20,420
Well, no, it kind of goes both ways.

1141
00:49:20,420 --> 00:49:21,380
Who's mom's favorite?

1142
00:49:21,380 --> 00:49:22,900
Who was trying to kill who first?

1143
00:49:22,900 --> 00:49:24,099
That's what I want to know.

1144
00:49:24,099 --> 00:49:25,940
One of them kind of has this like,

1145
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:30,260
gives a big sigh and scowls.

1146
00:49:31,780 --> 00:49:33,219
Which question am I answering?

1147
00:49:34,659 --> 00:49:36,500
Who was trying to kill who first question?

1148
00:49:37,139 --> 00:49:41,380
Well, I might have tried to

1149
00:49:42,340 --> 00:49:45,539
throw him under a wagon once or twice before.

1150
00:49:45,539 --> 00:49:47,220
Oh, so I guess we also know the answer

1151
00:49:47,220 --> 00:49:48,980
to the who's mom's favorite question.

1152
00:49:48,980 --> 00:49:50,980
Yeah, probably.

1153
00:49:51,940 --> 00:49:52,820
Not me.

1154
00:49:52,820 --> 00:49:53,700
Yeah, no, we got that.

1155
00:49:53,700 --> 00:49:54,500
Not Greg.

1156
00:49:54,500 --> 00:49:54,900
No.

1157
00:49:54,900 --> 00:49:55,460
Oh, Greg.

1158
00:49:55,460 --> 00:49:55,700
No.

1159
00:49:55,700 --> 00:49:56,500
Oh, Greg.

1160
00:49:56,500 --> 00:49:57,700
Oh, Greg.

1161
00:49:57,700 --> 00:50:00,340
Thru Dwenir over there.

1162
00:50:01,059 --> 00:50:01,860
What?

1163
00:50:01,860 --> 00:50:04,579
His name, Thru Dwenir.

1164
00:50:04,579 --> 00:50:07,220
Thru Dwenir and your name is Greg?

1165
00:50:07,220 --> 00:50:07,619
Thru Dwenir.

1166
00:50:08,420 --> 00:50:11,699
Yeah.

1167
00:50:13,059 --> 00:50:13,460
Okay.

1168
00:50:14,339 --> 00:50:16,259
Well, then I don't know if he's the favorite.

1169
00:50:17,059 --> 00:50:18,579
Wow, so not the favorite.

1170
00:50:18,579 --> 00:50:19,940
I think you may have gotten the.

1171
00:50:19,940 --> 00:50:20,420
I don't know.

1172
00:50:21,460 --> 00:50:23,460
I don't know which of those is better or worse.

1173
00:50:24,819 --> 00:50:26,659
I mean, one is more whimsical.

1174
00:50:26,659 --> 00:50:27,539
It's true, yes.

1175
00:50:27,539 --> 00:50:31,619
Thru Dwenir goes back in the rock racks quite many years.

1176
00:50:32,500 --> 00:50:35,299
Ah, yes, but the tale of Greg will live on.

1177
00:50:36,180 --> 00:50:38,660
I think you see why I'm up against Greg here.

1178
00:50:38,660 --> 00:50:40,420
The ballad of Greg.

1179
00:50:40,420 --> 00:50:40,740
Yes.

1180
00:50:42,340 --> 00:50:43,780
Oh, dear Sir Greg.

1181
00:50:46,660 --> 00:50:49,300
Okay, I think you guys just need to just quit it.

1182
00:50:50,260 --> 00:50:52,660
Greg, you need to move somewhere else.

1183
00:50:52,660 --> 00:50:54,180
Don't live in your brother's shadow.

1184
00:50:54,180 --> 00:50:54,900
That's bullshit.

1185
00:50:54,900 --> 00:50:57,460
Yeah, make your own way.

1186
00:50:57,460 --> 00:50:58,980
Why do I gotta move?

1187
00:50:58,980 --> 00:50:59,860
We don't got to.

1188
00:50:59,860 --> 00:51:01,539
You have the opportunity to.

1189
00:51:03,220 --> 00:51:03,539
Right.

1190
00:51:03,539 --> 00:51:06,340
Okay, so.

1191
00:51:06,340 --> 00:51:06,579
Right.

1192
00:51:06,579 --> 00:51:07,219
Stop thinking.

1193
00:51:07,219 --> 00:51:07,619
Poor me.

1194
00:51:07,619 --> 00:51:08,259
Poor me.

1195
00:51:08,259 --> 00:51:08,820
Oh, no, man.

1196
00:51:08,820 --> 00:51:09,219
Okay.

1197
00:51:09,219 --> 00:51:11,219
Hey, you gotta make your own breaks in this world, Greg.

1198
00:51:11,219 --> 00:51:11,779
Okay.

1199
00:51:11,779 --> 00:51:12,099
Yeah.

1200
00:51:12,659 --> 00:51:13,219
Yeah.

1201
00:51:13,219 --> 00:51:13,539
Okay.

1202
00:51:14,259 --> 00:51:14,659
Great.

1203
00:51:14,659 --> 00:51:16,420
You hear that Thru Dwenir?

1204
00:51:16,420 --> 00:51:16,659
Yeah.

1205
00:51:17,539 --> 00:51:19,380
See, I'm going to go with these folks.

1206
00:51:20,900 --> 00:51:23,139
And we're going to make our own path.

1207
00:51:23,139 --> 00:51:24,420
Oh, no.

1208
00:51:25,619 --> 00:51:26,500
What?

1209
00:51:26,500 --> 00:51:29,860
The other dwarf who you now know is Thru Dwenir.

1210
00:51:29,860 --> 00:51:30,420
So fine.

1211
00:51:31,380 --> 00:51:32,179
No one cares.

1212
00:51:33,140 --> 00:51:35,540
See if anybody will cry that you don't come home.

1213
00:51:35,540 --> 00:51:35,780
Bye.

1214
00:51:37,140 --> 00:51:38,260
He begins walking off.

1215
00:51:38,820 --> 00:51:39,620
All right, friends.

1216
00:51:41,060 --> 00:51:43,220
Looks like we have some adventuring to do.

1217
00:51:44,100 --> 00:51:47,620
You've freed me from my hostile family.

1218
00:51:48,260 --> 00:51:50,020
I turned my back while he was talking.

1219
00:51:50,020 --> 00:51:51,540
I'm like, guys, I'm so sorry.

1220
00:51:52,980 --> 00:51:54,500
This seems to happen a lot, I feel.

1221
00:51:56,420 --> 00:51:58,100
You're just a natural born leader.

1222
00:51:58,100 --> 00:51:59,140
People want to follow you.

1223
00:52:00,500 --> 00:52:01,540
I think it's true.

1224
00:52:01,539 --> 00:52:04,739
You've adopted two strays and a goat in the last 12 hours.

1225
00:52:08,739 --> 00:52:10,579
Three strays if you count Perseus.

1226
00:52:10,579 --> 00:52:11,139
Oh, yeah.

1227
00:52:11,139 --> 00:52:12,739
Well, we can't forget about Perseus.

1228
00:52:13,460 --> 00:52:14,340
Who's a Perseus?

1229
00:52:14,340 --> 00:52:15,779
Oh, this is Perseus.

1230
00:52:15,779 --> 00:52:17,380
And he climbs out of my pocket.

1231
00:52:17,380 --> 00:52:19,699
Oh, got a little rodent friend.

1232
00:52:19,699 --> 00:52:22,659
Do you also have an animal companion with you?

1233
00:52:22,659 --> 00:52:23,619
No, do I need one?

1234
00:52:23,619 --> 00:52:24,179
I can go find one.

1235
00:52:24,179 --> 00:52:24,739
No, it's all right.

1236
00:52:24,739 --> 00:52:26,340
We're just practically a zoo already.

1237
00:52:26,340 --> 00:52:28,019
I just wanted to get a full head count.

1238
00:52:28,019 --> 00:52:30,420
I need a drink and I wander back into the forest.

1239
00:52:31,220 --> 00:52:31,940
I like to drink.

1240
00:52:33,139 --> 00:52:34,820
Greg follows in behind you.

1241
00:52:34,820 --> 00:52:37,460
All right, Greg, you go, we'll go grab your bow

1242
00:52:37,460 --> 00:52:39,220
and then you can come pick up this firewood

1243
00:52:39,220 --> 00:52:41,780
and we'll go, we'll get you to Waterdeep, my friend.

1244
00:52:41,780 --> 00:52:42,579
Oh, cool.

1245
00:52:42,579 --> 00:52:44,099
I've never been to Waterdeep before.

1246
00:52:45,460 --> 00:52:46,500
Looking forward to this.

1247
00:52:46,500 --> 00:52:48,019
I got to carry all this firewood though?

1248
00:52:48,659 --> 00:52:49,780
Yeah, I mean.

1249
00:52:49,780 --> 00:52:50,820
Oh, that seems fair.

1250
00:52:50,820 --> 00:52:52,980
Yeah, I'm a long, I'm a team player.

1251
00:52:53,619 --> 00:52:55,300
I help him carry the firewood.

1252
00:52:56,340 --> 00:53:00,180
I like how I immediately hate any NPC you bring

1253
00:53:00,180 --> 00:53:02,820
at us. I always have the same reaction.

1254
00:53:02,820 --> 00:53:04,580
It's, oh, god damn it.

1255
00:53:07,460 --> 00:53:08,820
Fucking Greg now.

1256
00:53:08,820 --> 00:53:12,420
Greg, Greg Grancis, god damn it.

1257
00:53:13,380 --> 00:53:15,220
So what's your story there, friend?

1258
00:53:15,220 --> 00:53:20,260
Did you get, you guys been together a long time?

1259
00:53:20,260 --> 00:53:21,220
Oh, no.

1260
00:53:21,220 --> 00:53:22,260
No, stray.

1261
00:53:22,260 --> 00:53:24,820
Yeah, I just met these guys earlier.

1262
00:53:24,820 --> 00:53:27,060
They busted me out of the pokey.

1263
00:53:28,740 --> 00:53:29,240
Oh.

1264
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:30,600
But it was okay.

1265
00:53:30,600 --> 00:53:32,200
I mean, I helped them fight some zombies

1266
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:34,680
and they got like sucked into a portal.

1267
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:37,960
Traveling with some prisoners?

1268
00:53:37,960 --> 00:53:39,880
Yeah, you know, pretty run-of-the-mill stuff for us.

1269
00:53:39,880 --> 00:53:41,560
Yeah, no, that's cool.

1270
00:53:41,560 --> 00:53:43,000
Do you know who these guys are?

1271
00:53:45,240 --> 00:53:46,840
Well, they looked very familiar

1272
00:53:46,840 --> 00:53:51,480
and his cadence was very commanding.

1273
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:53,080
Have you heard of Flint and Thea?

1274
00:53:53,080 --> 00:53:53,720
And that beard.

1275
00:53:55,560 --> 00:53:57,880
Yeah, Flint and Thea, the decimators of dragons.

1276
00:53:57,880 --> 00:53:58,920
And Eulara.

1277
00:53:58,920 --> 00:54:02,599
And Eulara, yeah, they're all very great saviors.

1278
00:54:04,119 --> 00:54:06,200
We never run into just on the road.

1279
00:54:06,200 --> 00:54:07,240
What do you mean this is them?

1280
00:54:07,240 --> 00:54:08,840
That's Flint and that's Thea.

1281
00:54:09,800 --> 00:54:13,960
Oh, maybe I shouldn't have shot at them with an arrow.

1282
00:54:14,519 --> 00:54:16,119
I wasn't too worried about it.

1283
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:20,119
Besides, I recovered Brunor Battle Hammer's battle axe.

1284
00:54:20,119 --> 00:54:20,599
So we're good.

1285
00:54:20,599 --> 00:54:21,800
Seriously, it's not a fake?

1286
00:54:22,599 --> 00:54:23,800
Nah, real deal, baby.

1287
00:54:24,519 --> 00:54:25,480
Where'd you get it from?

1288
00:54:25,480 --> 00:54:27,480
Baby's, baby's happening.

1289
00:54:28,440 --> 00:54:30,199
Yeah, a little magic spell got it for me.

1290
00:54:30,199 --> 00:54:31,159
Don't you worry about it.

1291
00:54:31,159 --> 00:54:31,659
Wow.

1292
00:54:33,240 --> 00:54:34,039
That's really cool.

1293
00:54:36,119 --> 00:54:38,199
Okay, so I'm traveling with the people

1294
00:54:38,199 --> 00:54:40,119
who saved the world and the prisoner.

1295
00:54:42,840 --> 00:54:43,960
We also saved.

1296
00:54:45,079 --> 00:54:45,719
Former prisoner.

1297
00:54:45,719 --> 00:54:46,679
Jailbird, if you will.

1298
00:54:48,679 --> 00:54:49,880
I didn't commit a crime.

1299
00:54:50,519 --> 00:54:52,119
I didn't want to join an evil plot.

1300
00:54:53,639 --> 00:54:56,039
You guys get back to the campsite

1301
00:54:56,119 --> 00:54:58,679
and drop the firewood.

1302
00:54:59,239 --> 00:55:01,079
And he looks up at the wagon and says,

1303
00:55:01,079 --> 00:55:02,279
is there, is there, is there...

1304
00:55:04,279 --> 00:55:05,079
That's just Donnie.

1305
00:55:05,079 --> 00:55:05,320
Yeah.

1306
00:55:05,320 --> 00:55:05,880
Don't you worry about him.

1307
00:55:05,880 --> 00:55:08,039
I was not joking when I was slapping you

1308
00:55:08,039 --> 00:55:09,800
and telling you how he had a Wyrmling

1309
00:55:09,800 --> 00:55:11,239
who would destroy your group.

1310
00:55:11,239 --> 00:55:13,719
I thought you were being paid to say that at that point.

1311
00:55:16,679 --> 00:55:19,960
Okay, I'm just, I'm going to go get some more firewood

1312
00:55:21,159 --> 00:55:23,880
and I'll be back in a second.

1313
00:55:23,880 --> 00:55:24,679
I don't think he's going to be back.

1314
00:55:24,679 --> 00:55:25,480
Sure, we'll be here.

1315
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:26,440
Okay, cool.

1316
00:55:26,440 --> 00:55:27,559
Yeah, it's good.

1317
00:55:27,559 --> 00:55:28,920
Good to see you guys.

1318
00:55:28,920 --> 00:55:29,719
I'll be right back.

1319
00:55:29,719 --> 00:55:31,559
Yeah, be nice to your brother.

1320
00:55:31,559 --> 00:55:32,599
I don't know what you're talking about.

1321
00:55:32,599 --> 00:55:33,480
I'll be right back soon.

1322
00:55:36,599 --> 00:55:39,079
Inside my bag of holding,

1323
00:55:39,079 --> 00:55:42,280
I bring out a tankard of beer and many glasses.

1324
00:55:48,679 --> 00:55:49,639
I don't know about you guys,

1325
00:55:51,240 --> 00:55:54,440
but a horde of zombies in a disappearing city

1326
00:55:54,440 --> 00:55:55,559
makes me want to drink.

1327
00:55:55,559 --> 00:55:56,519
Yeah, I'm into it.

1328
00:55:56,519 --> 00:55:57,720
Yeah, that'd be nice.

1329
00:55:58,920 --> 00:56:00,519
Hey, Donnie, you going to light this fire, buddy?

1330
00:56:05,800 --> 00:56:06,280
There you go.

1331
00:56:07,559 --> 00:56:08,280
Thanks.

1332
00:56:08,280 --> 00:56:09,240
It's lit.

1333
00:56:09,240 --> 00:56:11,880
You got any, you cooking up any good stuff?

1334
00:56:11,880 --> 00:56:14,200
You catch any animals out there?

1335
00:56:14,200 --> 00:56:15,639
I throw him a piece of bread.

1336
00:56:16,200 --> 00:56:17,720
This isn't what I was looking for.

1337
00:56:17,720 --> 00:56:19,000
As if you're still hungry.

1338
00:56:19,000 --> 00:56:20,519
The carbs go straight to my hips.

1339
00:56:21,079 --> 00:56:22,760
That's what happens to all of us, Donnie.

1340
00:56:22,760 --> 00:56:24,600
Oh, all right.

1341
00:56:24,600 --> 00:56:25,560
Well, at least it's not me.

1342
00:56:27,960 --> 00:56:30,520
And unless you specifically want to talk about anything else,

1343
00:56:30,520 --> 00:56:31,640
Greg does not return.

1344
00:56:32,600 --> 00:56:33,240
What?

1345
00:56:33,240 --> 00:56:33,880
Shocking.

1346
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:34,840
Weird.

1347
00:56:34,840 --> 00:56:40,040
The night rolls on without incident as we fade into the next day.

1348
00:56:53,160 --> 00:57:02,760
The song Nowhere Land is by Kavin McLeod of Incompetech.Filmmusic.io.

1349
